overview: The user initiated a review process for a recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application. The primary goal was to verify that the
  application, including its database and API endpoints, fully met the
  acceptance criteria outlined in the provided Statement of Work and
  questionnaire details. The assistant's approach involved systematically
  reading through key files in the codebase. This included examining the
  questionnaire's outline, data types, validation schemas, Prisma database
  schema, API routes for responses, CSV export, and PDF generation, as well as
  core UI components for the questionnaire form, admin dashboard, and individual
  sections like demographics and daytime sleepiness. This comprehensive file
  review was conducted to gather all necessary information before providing a
  detailed assessment of the implementation against the specified requirements.
